The paper discusses the use of machine and deep learning-based algorithms for prediction problems in time series, specifically in the financial domain. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence and machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv. The paper specifically focuses on the comparison of LSTM and BiLSTM models, which are commonly used in deep learning for time series analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of financial time series data, which could also fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
